{
  "stem": "3874.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But the life in Eaubonne and Villa Chesnaie was really very pleasant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We were taught.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "First of all, we had to learn French.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "All the kids that were there were from Germany and Austria.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They were a few, I think, from Belgium.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Most of them were-- well, in Villa Chesnaie, and in Eaubonne, it was the religious kids.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Well, we were somewhat religious at home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But when I talk religious in Eaubonne, I mean they were ultra orthodox.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I mean, really, ultra orthodox.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It was-- I mean, it was like the hasid.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And that just wasn't me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But you know, children want to adapt.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So I adapted to that lifestyle.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I mean, every morning it was [NON-ENGLISH], every evening it was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We had Shabbats, we-- we went to synagogues.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We went to synagogues on Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We started learning French.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "They set up actually schools in the homes, themselves.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "The three homes, by the way, that the OSE then had, which were Montmorency, in Eaubonne and in Soisy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "They were all in walking distance of each other-- a couple of miles possibly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't recognize it at the time, because it seemed like a shop.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like I was the youngest kid who was in the carpenter shop.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I learned to be-- I was basically an apprentice cabinet maker.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most of the teachers or the counselors who were taking care of the children were also refugees from Germany and Austria-- many of them teachers, professors, doctors, what have you.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The director of the home, at the time, and it was a-- [NON-ENGLISH], his wife was a doctor.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she was the home doctor for-- she was a GP-- for everybody.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
